      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REFERENT POWER (2) has a terrific record this track and trip with three wins and one placing from four starts. Recorded a nose win (22.85) in a Other last time at this track. With a clean break looks hard to beat. LONG GULLY ASH (7) jumped from a middle draw last time and could manage only fourth and beaten 4.5 lengths (23.07) at this track. Has a good record here at this journey. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to his credit. Should be about the mark. JASON ROSE (5) was prominent throughout when winning in one of the fastest times of the card two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 4th and beaten 9 lengths at Angle Park (19.99). Speedy beginner who can find the front with a clean break from the middle of the draw. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. CHICKEN KNIGHT (1) has top-three aspirations after placing last time.",
